THE number of people that have tested positive for the Coronavirus has reached 116. There has been an increase of 31 new cases reported since yesterday's announcement. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize confirmed in a statement yesterday that 23 new infections have been recorded, however, on Wednesday morning 31 more cases were confirmed. According to the minister, 14 of the infections were transmitted locally, while the others have a history of travelling internationally. President Cyril Ramaphosa recently declared a state of disaster, officially prohibiting mass gathering of more than 100 people or more. The president has also announced international travel restrictions to prevent the spreading of the virus.  